---
import LegalLayout from "~/layouts/LegalLayout.astro";
import { getLocalizedPath } from "~/i18n/utils";

const privacy = getLocalizedPath("/privacy", "en");
const subprocessors = getLocalizedPath("/subprocessors", "en");

const title = "AwesomeBot Terms of Service";
const description =
  "Terms of Service for AwesomeBot — a 24/7 AI front desk for medical clinics and property managers. Use, obligations and liability.";
---

<LegalLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  eyebrow="Legal document"
  heading="Terms of Service"
  lastUpdated="Effective 10 July 2026"
  slugs={{ pl: "/regulamin", en: "/terms" }}
>
  <p class="legal-lead">
    These Terms govern the use of the AwesomeBot product and the website presenting it. We keep the
    rules clear and in plain language, with no hidden clauses.
  </p>

  <div class="legal-card">
    <p>
      <strong>Provider:</strong> Awesome Works AI Rafał Łazicki (sole proprietorship), ul. Wojska
      Polskiego 43, Warsaw, Poland, VAT ID PL5223202536 (the "<strong>Provider</strong>", "<strong>AwesomeWorks</strong>",
      "<strong>we</strong>").
    </p>
    <p><strong>Contact for all matters:</strong> hello@awesomeworks.ai</p>
  </div>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">§1</span>General provisions and definitions</h2>
  <p>
    These Terms set out how AwesomeWorks provides services electronically through the AwesomeBot
    product and how the product website (the "<strong>Landing</strong>") may be used. They are made
    available free of charge in a form that can be retrieved, reproduced and stored at any time.
  </p>
  <p>Definitions:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>AwesomeBot / the Service</strong> — SaaS software acting as a 24/7 AI front desk for
      service businesses, in particular medical clinics and property managers, housing communities
      and cooperatives. AwesomeBot receives contacts across phone, SMS, email and voice conversation
      (in the browser and by phone), recognises cases, sets priorities with a reason, groups reports,
      prepares reply drafts and performs selected internal actions.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Client</strong> — a business (e.g. a medical clinic, property-management firm, housing
      community or cooperative) that has entered into an agreement with the Provider to use
      AwesomeBot and for which a workspace is created.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>User</strong> — an individual acting on behalf of the Client (owner, administrator or
      team member) granted access by the Provider.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Contacting person</strong> — a third party (e.g. patient, resident, tenant, vendor)
      whose message or call is handled in AwesomeBot on the Client's behalf.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Demo call</strong> — a Landing feature allowing you to request a demonstration
      conversation with an AI voice agent.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>GDPR</strong> — Regulation (EU) 2016/679 of the European Parliament and of the Council.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">§2</span>Scope of services</h2>
  <p>
    Under the Service, AwesomeWorks provides the Client with AwesomeBot on the terms set out here and
    in an individual agreement or order. Through the Landing we provide, free of charge, a product
    presentation, contact forms and the Demo call.
  </p>
  <h3>Nature of the service (artificial intelligence)</h3>
  <p>AwesomeBot uses AI models. By design:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>internal, reversible</strong> actions (setting priority, grouping, tagging, preparing
      reply drafts, an internal heads-up to the on-call person) may run automatically and leave a
      record in the audit trail;
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>outbound communication</strong> to a contacting person (email/SMS reply, vendor
      dispatch, invoice approval) requires a User's approval before it is sent.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    AI-generated output (classifications, priorities, transcripts, reply drafts) is
    <strong>assistive</strong>, may contain errors and is subject to review by the User. Decisions
    with effects on third parties are made by the Client.
  </p>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">§3</span>Conditions of use</h2>
  <p>
    The Service is intended for businesses. An account is created by the Provider under an agreement
    or order — <strong>self-service registration is not available</strong>. Access is granted only to
    Users designated by the Client, who receive login credentials (email and password). The User must
    protect these credentials and not share them with unauthorised persons. The Client is responsible
    for its Users' actions as for its own.
  </p>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">§4</span>Technical requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Using the Service requires: a device with internet access, an up-to-date browser with JavaScript
    and cookies enabled, and — for voice features — a microphone and the browser's permission to use
    it. Phone features require an active telephone line. We strive to keep the Service continuously
    available, subject to technical and maintenance breaks and events beyond the Provider's control
    (including third-party provider outages).
  </p>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">§5</span>Demo call</h2>
  <p>
    This feature lets you request a demonstration conversation with an AI voice agent by providing a
    phone number. By requesting a call, you declare that you are entitled to use the number provided
    and consent to an automated AI agent calling it. <strong>You are talking to an AI system</strong>,
    not a human; the conversation is for demonstration purposes.
  </p>
  <p>
    The feature is subject to abuse-prevention limits (including the number of calls per number and
    per IP address within 24 hours, and a minimum interval between calls). The Provider may refuse a
    call or temporarily restrict the feature. Processing of the data you provide is described in the
    <a href={privacy}>Privacy Policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">§6</span>The Client's obligations as data controller</h2>
  <p>
    For the personal data of contacting persons processed in AwesomeBot on the Client's behalf, the
    <strong>Client is the controller</strong> and AwesomeWorks acts as a <strong>processor</strong> —
    under a data processing agreement (DPA) forming part of the agreement with the Client. The Client
    undertakes in particular to:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>maintain a valid legal basis for processing data in AwesomeBot;</li>
    <li>
      meet its information obligation towards contacting persons, including — where applicable —
      informing them about <strong>call recording and transcription</strong> and the use of
      AwesomeBot and its subprocessors;
    </li>
    <li>
      where the Client is a medical clinic or otherwise processes special categories of data (e.g.
      health data, Art. 9 GDPR), ensure an appropriate legal basis for such processing; this
      processing is covered by the DPA;
    </li>
    <li>
      handle data-subject requests regarding contacting persons' data (we support the Client in
      fulfilling them).
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    The Client must not use the Service unlawfully, to send unsolicited marketing, or in a way that
    infringes third-party rights.
  </p>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">§7</span>Liability</h2>
  <p>
    AwesomeWorks provides the Service with due care but — given the use of AI models —
    <strong>does not guarantee that automatically generated content is error-free, complete or fit
    for a particular purpose</strong>. Final review and decision rest with the Client. We are not
    liable for the consequences of the Client's decisions based on AI output, nor for the content of
    outbound communication approved by a User. The Provider's liability towards the Client (a
    business) is limited to the extent permitted by law; details are set out in the agreement. These
    limitations do not apply where excluding liability is not permitted (including wilful misconduct).
  </p>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">§8</span>Payments</h2>
  <p>
    AwesomeBot is a paid service on the terms set out in the Client's agreement or order. Landing
    features, including the Demo call, are free of charge. Pricing, billing periods and invoicing are
    governed by the agreement with the Client.
  </p>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">§9</span>Complaints</h2>
  <p>
    Complaints regarding the Service or the Landing may be submitted to hello@awesomeworks.ai. A
    complaint should include a description of the matter and contact details. We handle complaints
    promptly, no later than within 14 days, and inform you of the outcome at the address provided.
  </p>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">§10</span>Personal data</h2>
  <p>
    The processing of personal data — the controller and processor roles, data categories, legal
    bases, retention periods and data-subject rights — is described in the
    <a href={privacy}>Privacy Policy</a>. The entities processing data on our behalf are listed in
    the <a href={subprocessors}>Subprocessor List</a>.
  </p>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">§11</span>Term and termination</h2>
  <p>
    The term and termination of the AwesomeBot agreement are set out in the agreement with the
    Client. Use of the Landing and free features may be ended at any time by ceasing to use them.
    After the engagement ends, workspace data is deleted or returned in line with the Privacy Policy
    and the DPA.
  </p>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">§12</span>Changes to the Terms</h2>
  <p>
    The Provider may change these Terms for important reasons (changes in law, the scope of the
    Service, security requirements or providers). We give reasonable advance notice by email
    associated with the workspace or via an in-service notice. The current version is published on
    the Landing with its effective date.
  </p>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">§13</span>Final provisions</h2>
  <p>
    These Terms are governed by Polish law. Matters not regulated here are subject to generally
    applicable law, including the Civil Code, the Act on Providing Services by Electronic Means and
    the GDPR. Disputes arising from the Service provided to a business are resolved by the court with
    jurisdiction over the Provider's registered seat.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
